# Cursor / Codex Rules — Authoritative

**Context File Philosophy:** Research (Gloaguen et al., 2026) shows that comprehensive context files reduce agent performance by ~3% and increase costs by 20%+. Minimal developer-written files improve performance by ~4%. This `.cursorrules` file is intentionally minimal—only essential constraints, no comprehensive documentation.

## Scope
- Work ONLY inside this repository
- Never access files outside the repo
- No system, environment, or user-config changes

## AI Role (Global)
- Advisory only
- No autonomous execution
- No delegation or background agents
- Human is always the final decision-maker

## Codex-Specific Rules
- Codex is advisory-only (drafts, explanations, suggestions)
- Codex MUST NOT apply changes automatically
- Codex MUST NOT plan or execute multi-step tasks autonomously
- Codex MUST NOT make architecture or design decisions
- Codex MUST NOT touch security-critical code unless explicitly requested
- Codex MUST NOT run shell commands unless explicitly requested

## Workflow
- One task per interaction
- Diff-first always (unified diff)
- Never auto-apply changes
- Human review required before acceptance
- Verification required (tests or exact repro commands)

## Limits
- Max 200 lines per diff
- No refactors unless explicitly requested
- No new dependencies unless explicitly requested
